---
import StaticArticlePage from '@/components/ui/StaticArticlePage.astro'
import { getLegalContactLinks } from '@/lib/legal-contact'
import {
  getLegalGoverningLaw,
  getLegalOperatorLocation,
  getLegalOperatorName,
  getLegalTemplateNotice,
  getLegalVenue,
  siteConfig,
} from '@/lib/site-config'
import { resolveLocaleHrefMap } from '@/lib/locale-config'
import { getTermsHref } from '@/lib/terms-links'
import { getSiteLocale, type SiteLocale } from '@/lib/site-copy'

type Props = {
  locale?: SiteLocale
}

const { locale: requestedLocale = 'en' } = Astro.props
const locale = getSiteLocale(requestedLocale)
const isPortuguese = locale === 'pt-br'
const { legalEmail, supportEmail } = getLegalContactLinks()
const contactEmails = [legalEmail, supportEmail].filter((email) => email !== null)
const operatorName = getLegalOperatorName(locale)
const operatorLocation = getLegalOperatorLocation(locale)
const governingLaw = getLegalGoverningLaw(locale)
const venue = getLegalVenue(locale)
const templateNotice = getLegalTemplateNotice(locale)
const localeHrefs = resolveLocaleHrefMap((supportedLocale) => getTermsHref(supportedLocale))
---

<StaticArticlePage
  description={
    isPortuguese
      ? `Termos-base para uso de ${siteConfig.site.name} e dos recursos relacionados.`
      : `Starter terms for using ${siteConfig.site.name} and related features.`
  }
  kicker="Legal"
  localeHrefs={localeHrefs}
  title={isPortuguese ? 'Termos de Uso' : 'Terms of Service'}
>
  <blockquote>
    <p>
      <strong>{isPortuguese ? 'Aviso de template.' : 'Template note.'}</strong> {templateNotice}
    </p>
  </blockquote>

  {isPortuguese ? (
    <>
      <p>
        Estes Termos de Uso sao um ponto de partida reutilizavel para projetos feitos com este
        template. Eles regem o acesso a {siteConfig.site.name} e a qualquer conteudo, conta, download,
        newsletter ou recurso de produto que o operador resolver habilitar.
      </p>

      <h2>Quem opera o site</h2>
      <p>
        {operatorName} opera {siteConfig.site.name} a partir de {operatorLocation}. Nestes termos, "nos"
        se refere a esse operador e ao projeto construido sobre este template.
      </p>

      <h2>Uso aceitavel</h2>
      <p>Voce so pode usar o site para fins licitos e sem prejudicar a plataforma ou outras pessoas.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Nao interfira no site, na infraestrutura ou nos controles de seguranca</li>
        <li>Nao faca scraping nem reutilize o conteudo de forma abusiva ou sem autorizacao</li>
        <li>Nao envie spam, malware, material ilegal ou conteudo enganoso</li>
        <li>Nao deturpe sua identidade nem sua relacao com empresa, marca ou organizacao</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Contas e recursos opcionais</h2>
      <p>
        Algumas implementacoes podem adicionar contas, comentarios, assinaturas, pagamentos, downloads
        ou outros recursos restritos. Quando esses recursos existirem, usuarios devem fornecer dados
        corretos e manter suas credenciais seguras.
      </p>

      <h2>Conteudo e propriedade intelectual</h2>
      <p>
        Salvo indicacao em contrario, estrutura do site, design e conteudo original pertencem ao
        operador ou aos seus licenciadores. Usuarios podem compartilhar links e citar trechos curtos
        com atribuicao, mas reutilizacao maior depende da licenca ou das permissoes publicadas naquela
        instalacao.
      </p>

      <h2>Sem aconselhamento profissional</h2>
      <p>
        Este template costuma ser usado em projetos editoriais ou educacionais. O conteudo publicado em
        cima dele deve ser tratado como informacao geral, salvo quando o operador declarar algo mais
        especifico.
      </p>

      <h2>Servicos de terceiros</h2>
      <p>
        Projetos criados a partir deste template podem depender de hospedagem, analytics, auth,
        comentarios, email ou pagamentos. Esses provedores operam sob seus proprios termos e politicas.
      </p>

      <h2>Disponibilidade e mudancas</h2>
      <p>
        O operador pode atualizar, pausar, renomear, limitar ou encerrar partes do site a qualquer
        momento. Estes termos tambem podem mudar conforme o produto ou as exigencias legais mudarem.
      </p>

      <h2>Isencao e limitacao de responsabilidade</h2>
      <p>
        O site pode ser fornecido "como esta" e "conforme disponivel" na maior extensao permitida por
        lei. Revise e adapte esta clausula para a jurisdicao, o modelo de negocio e o risco real do
        projeto antes do lancamento.
      </p>

      <h2>Lei aplicavel e foro</h2>
      <p>
        Este documento-base assume que disputas sao regidas por {governingLaw} e tratadas em {venue}.
        Troque esta secao pela lei, pelo foro e pelas regras obrigatorias de consumo que realmente se
        aplicam a sua operacao.
      </p>

      {contactEmails.length > 0 ? (
        <>
          <h2>Contato</h2>
          <p>
            Para notificacoes juridicas ou duvidas de suporte relacionadas a estes termos, entre em
            contato por{' '}
            {contactEmails.map((email, index) => (
              <>
                {index > 0 ? (index === contactEmails.length - 1 ? ' ou ' : ', ') : null}
                <a href={email.href}>{email.value}</a>
              </>
            ))}
            .
          </p>
        </>
      ) : null}
    </>
  ) : (
    <>
      <p>
        These Terms of Service are a reusable starting point for projects built on this template. They
        govern access to {siteConfig.site.name} and to any content, accounts, downloads, newsletters, or
        product features the operator decides to enable.
      </p>

      <h2>Who operates the site</h2>
      <p>
        {operatorName} operates {siteConfig.site.name} from {operatorLocation}. In these terms, "we" refers
        to that operator and the project built on this template.
      </p>

      <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
      <p>You may use the site only for lawful purposes and in a way that does not harm the platform or other users.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Do not interfere with the site, its infrastructure, or its security controls</li>
        <li>Do not scrape or reuse the content in abusive or unauthorized ways</li>
        <li>Do not upload spam, malware, unlawful material, or deceptive content</li>
        <li>Do not misrepresent your identity or your relationship with a company or brand</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Accounts and optional features</h2>
      <p>
        Some deployments may add accounts, comments, subscriptions, payments, downloads, or other
        gated features. When those features exist, users must provide accurate information and keep
        their credentials secure.
      </p>

      <h2>Content and intellectual property</h2>
      <p>
        Unless stated otherwise, the site structure, design, and original content belong to the
        operator or its licensors. Users may share links and quote limited excerpts with attribution,
        but broader reuse depends on the license or permissions published for that deployment.
      </p>

      <h2>No professional advice</h2>
      <p>
        This template is commonly used for editorial or educational projects. Content published on top
        of it should be treated as general information unless the operator clearly states otherwise.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-party services</h2>
      <p>
        Projects built from this template may rely on providers such as hosting, analytics, auth,
        comments, email, or payments. Those providers operate under their own terms and policies.
      </p>

      <h2>Availability and changes</h2>
      <p>
        The operator may update, pause, rename, limit, or discontinue parts of the site at any time.
        These terms may also change as the product or legal requirements change.
      </p>

      <h2>Disclaimer and limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>
        The site may be provided on an "as is" and "as available" basis to the maximum extent allowed
        by law. Review and adapt this clause to match the jurisdiction, business model, and actual risk
        profile of the project before launch.
      </p>

      <h2>Governing law and venue</h2>
      <p>
        This starter document assumes that disputes are governed by {governingLaw} and handled in {venue}.
        Replace this section with the real law, forum, and mandatory consumer rules that apply to your
        operation.
      </p>

      {contactEmails.length > 0 ? (
        <>
          <h2>Contact</h2>
          <p>
            For legal notices or support questions related to these terms, contact{' '}
            {contactEmails.map((email, index) => (
              <>
                {index > 0 ? (index === contactEmails.length - 1 ? ' or ' : ', ') : null}
                <a href={email.href}>{email.value}</a>
              </>
            ))}
            .
          </p>
        </>
      ) : null}
    </>
  )}
</StaticArticlePage>
